Package: survblendr
Type: Package
Title: Adaptive Spline-Weighted Blending for Survival Extrapolation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hao", "Chen", email = "hche2036@uni.sydney.edu.au", role = c("aut","cre"))
)
Description: One-shot survival extrapolation combining a piecewise-exponential
    model fitted via INLA over the observed window with an anchored Gompertz tail,
    blended on the cumulative-hazard scale using monotone P-spline weights.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/haohaostats/survblendr, https://haohaostats.github.io/survblendr
BugReports: https://github.com/haohaostats/survblendr/issues
Depends: R (>= 4.0)
Imports:
    stats,
    utils,
    ggplot2,
    survival,
    INLA,
    mgcv,
    scam,
    withr
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    pkgdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
Language: en-US
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Additional_repositories: https://inla.r-inla-download.org/R/stable
